<% title "RI Assessment Results" %>

<hr />

<p>
  <strong>Name:</strong>
  <%=h @survey.first_name %> 
  <%=h @survey.last_name %>
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Email:</strong>
  <%=h @survey.email %>
</p>

<div class="chart">
  <img src="http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?chs=220x115&chf=bg,s,272830&chco=771111,444411,117711,114444,111177&cht=gom&chl=You&chd=t:<%=h @survey.normalized_score %>" border=0 />
</div>

<p>
  <strong>Normalized Score:</strong>
  <%=h @survey.normalized_score %>
  <%# todo: helper functions / or use the class out there %>
</p>
<p><small>Your Normalized Score represents your relational intelligence measured on a scale from 1 to 100.
This number is an absolute rating and has no correlation to the general population.</small></p>

<p>
  <strong>Standardized RQ:</strong>
  <%=h @survey.std_rq %>
</p>
<p><small>Your Standardized RQ is a rough approximation of what your score might be if this assessment were
scored like a standard IQ test.  A score of 100 represents an average person on this scale</small></p>

<!-- Categories -->
<% cs = @survey.category_scores %>
<div class="chart">
  <%# This is what happens when a perl programmer finally learns ruby %>
  <img src="http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?chs=500x150&chf=bg,s,272830&chco=ccccbb,994433,553388,998833,449955,0c0c33,dd6633&cht=bvs&chd=t:<%= cs.compact.join(",") %>&chdl=<%=h ( (Category.all.sort { |x,y| x.id <=> y.id } ).collect { |x| x.title } ).join("|") %>" border=0 /> 
</div>

<p>
  <strong>Category Breakdown</strong>
</p>
<p><small>The chart above shows how well your relational weaknesses fit against some stereotypical 
scenarios painted in the book.  It might make sense to focus on the chapters that deal with the issues
identified here most strongly.</small></p>

